result.execSummary:
Jeanna M Lalli was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jeanna M Lalli was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:00 PM Prosecuting attorney Brian H. Wright Aty in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jeanna M Lalli appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Andrew T Knaak appeared by video for Jeanna M Lalli. 

This is an extradition request.
Defendant does not contest extradition and voluntarily agrees to extradition to return to Minnesota and indicates she will sign the same.
Court signs extradition.  Court security deputy will take court signed extradition document to jail for signature.
